content.problemStatement:
Chef has just finished practicing binary search and tries to perform it on permutations.

For a permutation PPP of length NNN, Chef wants to find a particular number XXX in the permutation.

To do this, he calls the function `binsearch`(P,1,N,X)(P, 1, N, X)(P,1,N,X):

`long long int binsearch(int P[], int L, int R, int X) {
    if(L&gt;R)
        return 0;
    int MID = (L + R) / 2;
    if(P[MID] == X || L == R)
        return P[MID];
    if(P[MID] &gt; X)
        return P[MID] + binsearch(P, L, MID - 1, X);
    if(P[MID] &lt; X)
        return P[MID] + binsearch(P, MID + 1, R, X);
}
`Note that the `binsearch` function returns the sum of the numbers that were traversed during the binary search algorithm until the element XXX is found or the search interval [L,R][L, R][L,R] becomes empty (it can happen that the function does not find XXX, since the permutation is not always sorted).

Chef provides you with two integers, NNN and MMM, and an array AAA containing MMM elements.

For each element AiA_iAi​, your task is to compute the **sum** of `binsearch`(P,1,N,Ai)(P, 1, N, A_i)(P,1,N,Ai​) across **all permutations** PPP of length NNN. Since the sum could be huge, compute it modulo 109+710^9 + 7109+7.

Note that a permutation of length NNN consists of all elements from 111 to NNN exactly once.


Input Format

The first line of input will contain two space-separated integers NNN and MMM, denoting the size of permutation and the size of array respectively.
The second line of input will contain MMM space-separated integers denoting elements of array AAA.


Output Format
Output MMM lines denoting the answer modulo 109+710^9 + 7109+7 for each element AiA_iAi​.

